cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is about face alignment using the Active Shape Model (ASM) and Support Vector Machine (SVM). The paper focuses on improving the performance of the ASM model for face alignment. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses SVM for landmark classification, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper deals with image processing techniques such as edge detection and filtering, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses databases for experimental results, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
